This paper deals with the representation and manipulation of knowledge in a domain of interest, as well as the actions that can be performed on this knowledge. This is a central topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the use of Description Logic (DL) and first-order mu-calculus are common tools in this field. The paper also deals with inconsistency handling, which is a topic in both databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a formalism for representing and reasoning about knowledge and actions, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO).
